<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-17T00:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-17T00:30:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">733.35/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay (<persName type="from">Wright</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-17T02:00:00-03:30">July 17,
                                    1932—2 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>42. My 41, July 16, midnight. Presence here of two United States Coast
                            Guard vessels offers possible opportunity for conference on board
                            between representatives of both Governments. <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">Bliss</persName> concurs in this suggestion. Please advise whether
                            we may be authorized to propose this to Uruguayan and Argentine
                            Governments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>